Agreed that the events fire, so I should have left the bug resolved and opened another bug for the new issues I mentioned.  My bad.  

FYI, the PrintWriter that is created in DataSource.beforeOpen was deliberately not closed because it is closed later in DataSource.afterOpen, after adding to the file.  Unfortunately, DataSource.afterOpen was also the method that had an unclosed quote, so my test code was never executed. It is nearly impossible to test JavaScript when a syntax error like a missing closing quote is not reported as an error to the developer.  But that is the subject of another bug.

